        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 10:29AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1029 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spring Hill, or 8 miles southeast of Hurtsboro, moving northeast at
45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ladonia, Rutherford, Russell County Sports Complex, Hatchechubbe,
Uchee Creek, Seale, Fort Mitchell, Ladonia Sports Complex, Fort
Mitchell Activity Center, Phenix Drag Strip, Phenix City, and
Parkmanville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
southeastern and east central Alabama.</instruction>
